Label: Bioassay Result
Description: A measured outcome or data point from a biological or biochemical experiment testing the effects of a substance

Label: Chemical Entity
Description: A molecule or compound with defined chemical structure and properties

Label: Chemical Identifier
Description: A unique code or number that identifies a specific chemical substance

Label: Database Entry
Description: A record or item stored in a scientific database

Label: Bioassay
Description: A laboratory test that measures the effects of a substance on living cells or organisms

Label: Chemical Structure Descriptor
Description: Information that describes the arrangement of atoms in a molecule

Label: Chemical Information
Description: Data or knowledge about chemical substances and properties

Label: Biological Target
Description: A molecule in a living system that a drug or substance interacts with

Label: Gene Identifier
Description: A unique code that identifies a specific gene

Label: Assay Design
Description: The specific method and conditions used to conduct a biological experiment

Label: May Inform On
Description: Indicates that assay data might provide information about a particular biological effect or toxicity

Label: Source
Description: The origin or reference for a piece of information

Label: Participates In
Description: An entity takes part in or is involved in a biological process

Label: Has Participant
Description: A process involves or includes a particular entity

Label: Type
Description: Specifies what category or class something belongs to

Label: Assay Source
Description: The organization or database that provided the experimental data

Label: UMLS Concept
Description: A unified medical term or concept from the medical terminology system

Label: In Vitro Assay Format
Description: The specific laboratory method used to test substances outside of living organisms

Label: Assay Tissue
Description: The type of biological tissue or cell used in the experiment

Label: Through Mechanistic Target
Description: The specific biological molecule through which a substance produces its effect

Label: Label
Description: A human-readable name for an entity

Label: Has Identifier
Description: Links an entity to its unique identification code

Label: Has Specified Output
Description: The result or product produced by a process or assay

Label: NCI Mechanistic Target
Description: The biological target classified according to National Cancer Institute terminology

Label: Assay Species
Description: The type of organism used in the biological experiment

Label: Has Assay Component
Description: The specific part or measurement within a larger bioassay

Label: Entrez Gene ID
Description: The unique identifier for a gene in the NCBI Entrez Gene database

Label: Has Unit
Description: Specifies the measurement unit for a numerical value

Label: Is About
Description: Indicates that information or data pertains to a particular subject

Label: Has Value
Description: Assigns a specific measurement or quantity to an entity

Label: Has Exposure
Description: Relates to the contact or treatment of a system with a substance
